// Stdlib: Modal Analysis Options, Modes & Results  (`std.modal.analysis`)
//
// PRD: docs/prds/v0_3/modal-analysis.md ¬ß4.1, ¬ß4.2, ¬ß4.3, ¬ß10 task Œ±.
//
// Provides the named-type surface for the v0.3 modal-analysis kernel:
//   - `DampingDescriptor`  ‚Äî marker trait for damping-strategy variants
//   - `NoDamping`          ‚Äî marker structure refining `DampingDescriptor`
//                            (undamped solve; default behaviour)
//   - `RayleighDamping`    ‚Äî proportional damping (alpha, beta) refining
//                            `DampingDescriptor`
//   - `Mode`               ‚Äî single (frequency, shape, participation, damping)
//                            modal eigenpair
//   - `ModalResult`        ‚Äî solver-output container (part, modes, BCs,
//                            damping, mass-/stiffness-matrix-norms)
//   - `ModalOptions`       ‚Äî solver-input knobs (n_modes, BCs, damping,
//                            sigma, tol, max_iters, reference_direction,
//                            element_order)
//
// Module placement: `std.modal.analysis` is the v0.3 sibling reserved by
// `std.trajectory`'s header ‚Äî "registered last ‚Ä¶ ready for the planned
// `std.modal` / `std.dynamics` siblings". Registered immediately BEFORE
// `std.trajectory` in `stdlib_loader.rs` so the v0.3 analysis cluster stays
// grouped at the tail of the loader vec, and so `ModalResult` is in the
// growing prelude for the future task that tightens trajectory.ri to consume
// `ModalResult.modes` (kinematic-completion PRD; not yet landed).
//
// `trait Support` from the much-earlier `std.fea.types` is already in
// the growing prelude at this point, so `List<Support>` resolves on both
// `ModalResult.boundary_conditions` and `ModalOptions.boundary_conditions`.
//
// Encoding notes:
//   1. Number-literal grammar is `\d+(\.\d+)?` (no scientific notation).
//      The PRD's `1e-9` default for `tol` therefore appears here as
//      `0.000000001`, same convention as `solver_buckling.ri`'s `tol = 1e-8`
//      ‚Üí `0.00000001`.
//   2. `ModalResult.part : String` is a PLACEHOLDER for the future `Part`
//      structure_def from the v0.3 solver-elastic PRD (not yet landed; see
//      `fea_multi_case.ri:269-273` placeholder convention). A FIXME comment
//      on the param flags the future tighten target.
//   3. `Mode.frequency : Frequency` carries the natural-frequency dimension
//      (`Frequency` = s‚Åª¬π, a registered named dimension). Tightened from the
//      former `Real` placeholder once `Frequency` gained a named scalar alias
//      (task 4548); the producer (modal_ops.rs) emits a dimensioned
//      `Value::Scalar { FREQUENCY }`. Contrast `fea_multi_case.ri::Load.force
//      : Real`, still a placeholder waiting for `Vector3<Force>`.
//   4. `Mode.shape : List<Vector3<Dimensionless>>` encodes mass-normalized
//      eigenvectors. Strictly, components of a mass-orthonormal mode shape
//      carry units of 1/‚àömass ‚Äî only the modal-mass scalar
//      m·µ¢ = Œ¶·µ¢·µÄ¬∑M¬∑Œ¶·µ¢ = kg ¬∑ (1/‚àökg)¬≤ is dimensionless under `Œ¶·µÄ¬∑M¬∑Œ¶ = I`
//      (PRD ¬ß4.1 + ¬ß7.5). Reify's dimension grammar has no SI-root extension,
//      so 1/‚àömass is not yet expressible; `Dimensionless` is the closest
//      encoding available today. (`Vector3<Real>` is not valid .ri syntax ‚Äî
//      the `Vector3<Q>` resolver requires `Q` to resolve to a
//      `DimensionVector`; `Real` is a primitive scalar, not a dimension
//      name.) Tightening to a future `Scalar<InvRootMass>` (or equivalent)
//      is left to the kinematic-completion sweep.
//   5. `ModalOptions.reference_direction : Vector3<Dimensionless>` is the
//      correct semantics (unit vector ‚Äî dimensionless). The constraint
//      `reference_direction.norm() > 0` is NOT expressible in Reify's
//      `constraint` grammar (method-call on Vector3, not a scalar predicate)
//      and is deferred to the runtime trampoline (future task Œ∂), mirroring
//      `BucklingOptions.mode` allowlist-deferral precedent
//      (solver_buckling.ri:97-107).

// ‚îÄ‚îÄ DampingDescriptor (marker trait) ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ

// `DampingDescriptor` is the marker trait for every damping-strategy variant
// (PRD ¬ß4.2). The Œ± phase declares two refining structures:
//   - `NoDamping`        ‚Äî undamped solve; semantically equivalent to
//                          RayleighDamping(alpha: 0, beta: 0) but a distinct
//                          type so the future `modal_analysis` trampoline can
//                          discriminate the no-damping fast path at dispatch.
//   - `RayleighDamping`  ‚Äî proportional damping Œ∂_i = (Œ± + Œ≤¬∑œâ_i¬≤) / (2¬∑œâ_i),
//                          where Œ± (mass-proportional) and Œ≤ (stiffness-
//                          proportional) are user-supplied. Preserves mode-
//                          shape orthogonality so transient response stays in
//                          real arithmetic.
//
// Kept empty by design (no required members): each variant carries its own
// per-strategy fields; the trait exists only to give the `damping` param on
// `ModalResult` / `ModalOptions` a single nominal type, so the eval-time
// dispatch matches via the SIR-Œ± nominal type-tag. Same pattern as
// `trait Support { }` (fea_types.ri) and `trait BoundaryCondition
// { }` (trajectory.ri).
trait DampingDescriptor { }

// ‚îÄ‚îÄ NoDamping ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ

// `NoDamping` is the zero-field marker structure for an undamped modal solve
// (PRD ¬ß4.2). Semantically equivalent to `RayleighDamping(alpha: 0, beta: 0)`
// but a distinct nominal type so the future `modal_analysis` trampoline can
// discriminate the no-damping fast path at dispatch via the SIR-Œ± nominal
// type-tag ‚Äî same dispatch mechanism `solve_elastic_static` uses to
// discriminate `PointLoad` vs `FixedSupport` in `fea_multi_case.ri`.
//
// PRD reference: docs/prds/v0_3/modal-analysis.md ¬ß4.2.
structure def NoDamping : DampingDescriptor { }

// ‚îÄ‚îÄ RayleighDamping ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ

// `RayleighDamping` is proportional damping parameterized by two scalars
// (PRD ¬ß4.2). The per-mode damping ratio is:
//
//     Œ∂_i = (Œ± + Œ≤ ¬∑ œâ_i¬≤) / (2 ¬∑ œâ_i)
//
// where œâ_i is the natural angular frequency of mode i (rad/s). This form
// preserves mode-shape orthogonality (the damping matrix C = Œ±¬∑M + Œ≤¬∑K
// commutes with M and K under the mass-orthonormal mode basis), so the
// transient response can be integrated mode-by-mode in real arithmetic
// rather than requiring a full complex-eigenvalue solve.
//
// Param semantics (PRD ¬ß4.2):
//   alpha ‚Äî mass-proportional damping coefficient (units 1/s). Damps low
//           frequencies more than high. Often calibrated from measured
//           damping ratio at the fundamental mode.
//   beta  ‚Äî stiffness-proportional damping coefficient (units s). Damps
//           high frequencies more than low. Useful for suppressing
//           high-frequency numerical noise from explicit time integration.
//
// Explicitly NOT constrained: alpha / beta are conventionally non-negative
// but physically meaningful at zero ("stiffness-only" damping with Œ±=0; or
// "mass-only" damping with Œ≤=0). Imposing `alpha >= 0` or `beta >= 0` at
// the structure-def level would forbid these special cases, so the contract
// stays open here. Mirrors solver_buckling.ri:97-107 "sigma is explicitly
// NOT constrained" discipline.
//
// PRD reference: docs/prds/v0_3/modal-analysis.md ¬ß4.2.
structure def RayleighDamping : DampingDescriptor {
    param alpha : Real
    param beta : Real
}

// ‚îÄ‚îÄ Mode ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ

// `Mode` is one modal eigenpair returned by the modal-analysis solver
// (PRD ¬ß4.1). Solver-populated only ‚Äî no caller-supplied defaults are
// meaningful, no scalar constraints (every field is solver-determined
// from the geometry / boundary conditions / damping).
//
// `Mode` coexists with `std.solver.buckling`'s `Mode` (same simple name,
// different modules). Per-module template storage and the first-wins
// shadow rule make this safe; if dual-import ambiguity ever surfaces at
// user call sites, the fallback rename is a one-line `.ri` change. See
// plan design-decision-6.
//
// Field semantics (PRD ¬ß4.1):
//   frequency          ‚Äî natural frequency œâ/(2œÄ) in Hz. Encoded as
//                        `Frequency` (= s‚Åª¬π, bare dimension name per the
//                        `HarmonicForce.frequency : Frequency` precedent
//                        below). Tightened from the former `Real` placeholder
//                        now that `Frequency` is a registered named dimension
//                        (task 4548); the modal producer (modal_ops.rs) emits
//                        a dimensioned `Value::Scalar { FREQUENCY }`.
//   shape              ‚Äî mass-normalized eigenvector (Œ¶·µÄ¬∑M¬∑Œ¶ = I) reshaped
//                        as per-node displacement-shaped vectors. Encoded
//                        as `List<Vector3<Dimensionless>>` as the closest
//                        encoding available today: strictly, components of
//                        a mass-orthonormal mode shape carry units of
//                        1/‚àömass (only the modal-mass scalar
//                        m·µ¢ = Œ¶·µ¢·µÄ¬∑M¬∑Œ¶·µ¢ is dimensionless per PRD ¬ß4.1 +
//                        ¬ß7.5). Reify's dimension grammar has no SI-root
//                        extension, so 1/‚àömass is not yet expressible;
//                        `Dimensionless` is the closest currently-resolvable
//                        spelling. (`Vector3<Real>` is not valid .ri syntax
//                        ‚Äî the `Vector3<Q>` resolver requires `Q` to be a
//                        dimension name; `Real` is a primitive scalar.)
//                        Tightening to a future `Scalar<InvRootMass>` (or
//                        equivalent) is left to the kinematic-completion
//                        sweep. (Contrast with buckling's `Mode.mode_shape
//                        : Field<Point3<Length>, Vector3<Length>>` where
//                        the Length parameterization is a typing
//                        convention, not a dimensional claim; see
//                        solver_buckling.ri:127-145 dimensionality note.)
//   participation_mass ‚Äî effective modal mass projected along the user-
//                        supplied reference_direction (PRD ¬ß4.3
//                        ModalOptions.reference_direction). Used to rank
//                        modes by importance for a given excitation
//                        direction. Encoded as `Real` as a PLACEHOLDER for
//                        `Scalar<Mass>` ‚Äî participation mass has the
//                        dimension of mass (kg under SI), but the
//                        named-scalar `Scalar<X>` alias has not landed
//                        anywhere in the stdlib yet. Same placeholder
//                        convention as `Load.force : Real` waiting for
//                        `Vector3<Force>` in `fea_multi_case.ri:269-296`.
//                        (`Mode.frequency` shared this convention until it was
//                        tightened to `Frequency` in task 4548.)
//   damping_ratio      ‚Äî Œ∂_i for this mode. Equals 0 for an undamped solve
//                        (`damping = NoDamping()`) or
//                        (Œ± + Œ≤¬∑œâ_i¬≤) / (2¬∑œâ_i) for proportional damping
//                        (`damping = RayleighDamping(Œ±, Œ≤)`).
structure def Mode {
    param frequency : Frequency
    param shape : List<Vector3<Dimensionless>>
    param participation_mass : Real
    param damping_ratio : Real
}

// ‚îÄ‚îÄ ModalResult ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ

// `ModalResult` is the modal-analysis solver-output container (PRD ¬ß4.1) ‚Äî
// the parallel sibling of `BucklingResult` (`std.solver.buckling`). Each
// instance bundles the computed eigenpairs together with the inputs they
// were solved against (boundary conditions, damping strategy) plus two
// matrix-norm diagnostics.
//
// Solver-populated only: every field is determined by the modal solve, so
// no caller-supplied defaults are meaningful. No scalar constraints are
// declared at the structure-def level ‚Äî the meaningful invariants here are
// COLLECTION invariants (`modes` non-empty, sorted ascending by frequency)
// which Reify's `constraint` grammar cannot express (it admits only scalar
// predicates over same-scope cells). These are producer-enforced by the
// future `modal_analysis` runtime trampoline (task Œ∂), mirroring the
// `BucklingResult.modes` discipline at solver_buckling.ri:196-205.
//
// Field semantics (PRD ¬ß4.1):
//   part                 ‚Äî the analysed part. FIXME(part-structdef, #4578): encoded
//                          as `String` PLACEHOLDER for the future `Part`
//                          structure_def from the v0.3 solver-elastic PRD
//                          (not yet landed). `String` (not `Real`) because
//                          `Part` semantically denotes a named entity /
//                          handle, consistent with the `FixedSupport.target
//                          : String` selector-placeholder precedent
//                          (fea_multi_case.ri:269-273 placeholder
//                          convention). Tightens to the `Part` type once it
//                          lands; consumer task Œ∂ reads `.modes`, not
//                          `.part`, so this placeholder is non-blocking.
//   modes                ‚Äî the computed modal eigenpairs, one `Mode` per
//                          extracted mode, ordered ascending by frequency.
//                          `Mode` is module-local so this resolves to
//                          `List<StructureRef("Mode")>`.
//   boundary_conditions  ‚Äî the support set the solve was constrained with.
//                          `Support` is the marker trait from
//                          `std.fea.types`, already in the growing
//                          prelude at modal-compile time, so this resolves
//                          to `List<TraitObject("Support")>` (same shape as
//                          trajectory's `List<BoundaryCondition>`).
//   damping              ‚Äî the damping strategy applied (`NoDamping` or
//                          `RayleighDamping`); trait-typed so eval-time
//                          dispatch matches via the SIR-Œ± nominal type-tag.
//   mass_matrix_norm     ‚Äî ‚ÄñM‚Äñ diagnostic (conditioning / sanity check).
//   stiffness_matrix_norm ‚Äî ‚ÄñK‚Äñ diagnostic (conditioning / sanity check).
//
// PRD reference: docs/prds/v0_3/modal-analysis.md ¬ß4.1.
structure def ModalResult {
    param part : String
    param modes : List<Mode>
    param boundary_conditions : List<Support>
    param damping : DampingDescriptor
    param mass_matrix_norm : Real
    param stiffness_matrix_norm : Real
    // NOTE ‚Äî explicitly NOT constrained:
    //   modes               : List<Mode>    ‚Äî collection invariants
    //                                          (non-empty, sorted ascending by
    //                                          frequency) are producer-enforced
    //                                          by the future modal_analysis
    //                                          trampoline (task Œ∂); Reify
    //                                          constraint clauses express only
    //                                          scalar predicates, not
    //                                          collection invariants. Mirrors
    //                                          BucklingResult.modes discipline
    //                                          (solver_buckling.ri:196-205).
    //   boundary_conditions : List<Support> ‚Äî collection of trait objects; no
    //                                          scalar invariant expressible.
    //   damping             : DampingDescriptor ‚Äî trait-typed; not scalar-
    //                                          predicable.
    //   part / *_norm       ‚Äî solver-populated outputs; no caller invariant.
}

// ‚îÄ‚îÄ ModalOptions ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ

// `ModalOptions` is the configuration object passed to the v0.3 modal
// eigensolver (PRD ¬ß4.3) ‚Äî the parallel sibling of `BucklingOptions`
// (`std.solver.buckling`). The scalar knobs carry sensible defaults (added
// in a later wave) so a caller overrides only the fields they care about;
// `boundary_conditions`, `damping`, and `reference_direction` are required
// at construction (no canonical default).
//
// Param semantics (PRD ¬ß4.3):
//   n_modes             ‚Äî eigenpair count to extract. Default 10 (added in a
//                          later step) covers the typical "first few modes"
//                          inspection workflow, mirroring
//                          `BucklingOptions.n_modes`.
//   boundary_conditions ‚Äî the support set constraining the eigenproblem.
//                          `Support` is the marker trait from
//                          `std.fea.types`, in the growing prelude at
//                          modal-compile time ‚Üí `List<TraitObject("Support")>`.
//                          Required at construction (no default).
//   damping             ‚Äî damping strategy (`NoDamping` for an undamped
//                          solve, `RayleighDamping(Œ±, Œ≤)` for proportional
//                          damping). Trait-typed so the eval-time trampoline
//                          dispatches via the SIR-Œ± nominal type-tag.
//                          Required at construction (no default in this wave;
//                          a trait-typed `= NoDamping()` default is deferred
//                          per plan design-decision-5).
//   sigma               ‚Äî spectral-shift origin (in eigenvalue units;
//                          dimensionless). Default `0.0` (added later) targets
//                          the smallest-|Œª| cluster (lowest-frequency modes).
//                          Explicitly NOT constrained: a shift can physically
//                          be anywhere on the real line (mirrors
//                          BucklingOptions.sigma).
//   tol                 ‚Äî eigensolver convergence tolerance. Default 1e-9
//                          (added later) encoded as the decimal literal
//                          `0.000000001` ‚Äî Reify's number grammar has no
//                          scientific notation (same convention as
//                          solver_buckling.ri:60-64).
//   max_iters           ‚Äî upper bound on total solver iterations across
//                          restarts. Default 200 (added later) per PRD ¬ß4.3
//                          (NOT 1000 ‚Äî modal converges faster than buckling).
//                          Exists so a pathologically conditioned problem
//                          fails loudly rather than running forever.
//   reference_direction ‚Äî unit excitation direction along which modal
//                          participation mass is projected (PRD ¬ß4.3).
//                          Encoded as `Vector3<Dimensionless>` ‚Äî a unit
//                          vector is genuinely dimensionless, so this is
//                          mathematically accurate (unlike `Mode.shape`,
//                          whose 1/‚àömass components are merely encoded as
//                          Dimensionless pending an SI-root grammar
//                          extension). `Vector3<Real>` is not valid .ri
//                          syntax ‚Äî the `Vector3<Q>` resolver requires `Q`
//                          to be a dimension name. Required at construction
//                          (no default ‚Äî there is no canonical excitation
//                          direction). The `reference_direction.norm() > 0`
//                          invariant is NOT expressible in Reify's
//                          `constraint` grammar (method-call on Vector3, not
//                          a scalar predicate) and is deferred to the runtime
//                          trampoline (future task Œ∂), mirroring
//                          `BucklingOptions.mode` allowlist-deferral
//                          (solver_buckling.ri:97-107). See plan
//                          design-decision-4.
//
// Defaults (PRD ¬ß4.3) ‚Äî literal-valued only, per plan design-decision-5:
//   (a) `tol = 0.000000001` is the decimal spelling of 1e-9. Reify's
//       number-literal grammar has no scientific notation, so the value is
//       written out long-hand (same convention as solver_buckling.ri:60-64
//       where `tol = 0.00000001` spells 1e-8). Strict-equality safe: the
//       IEEE-754 round-to-nearest of this exact decimal literal is
//       deterministic.
//   (b) `boundary_conditions`, `damping`, `reference_direction` are LEFT
//       DEFAULTLESS ‚Äî they are required at construction. This matches the
//       PRD ¬ß1 example usage, where every caller passes `boundary_conditions:`
//       and `damping:` explicitly and supplies an excitation
//       `reference_direction:` (there is no canonical default direction).
//   (c) A trait-typed default `damping = NoDamping()` is intentionally
//       DEFERRED to a follow-up: the trait-typed-default and Vector3-literal-
//       default code-paths are not exercised by any existing stdlib
//       structure_def, so adding them here would turn a 1-line .ri change
//       into uncharted compiler territory (plan design-decision-5). Callers
//       in PRD ¬ß1 already pass `damping:` explicitly, so there is no
//       API-surface regression.
//
// NOTE: the three positivity constraints land in step-18 ‚Äî declared
// constraintless here so the step-17 RED test fails before that impl.
//
// PRD reference: docs/prds/v0_3/modal-analysis.md ¬ß4.3.
structure def ModalOptions {
    param n_modes : Int = 10
    param boundary_conditions : List<Support>
    param damping : DampingDescriptor
    param sigma : Real = 0.0
    param tol : Real = 0.000000001            // = 1e-9 (no scientific notation in Reify grammar)
    param max_iters : Int = 200               // PRD ¬ß4.3 ‚Äî NOT 1000 (modal converges faster than buckling)
    param reference_direction : Vector3<Dimensionless>
    // Finite-element order for the (K, M) assembly. `ElementOrder.P1` (default,
    // first-order constant-strain tets) preserves back-compat for every existing
    // caller bit-for-bit; `ElementOrder.P2` (second-order, 10-node quadratic
    // tets) resolves bending curvature and removes the P1 bending lock, closing
    // the slender-beam modal-frequency error to ~2% (task 4066 ‚Äî the P2-tet
    // follow-up the prior 10% P1 floor deferred). `ElementOrder` is the shared
    // `std.solver.elastic` enum resolved via the growing prelude (task 4108);
    // declared exactly like `ElasticOptions.element_order` (solver_elastic.ri),
    // same default.
    param element_order : ElementOrder = ElementOrder.P1

    // A non-positive `n_modes` requests zero eigenmodes ‚Äî a degenerate solve.
    // Declaring the lower bound at the structure-def level makes the contract
    // explicit in production code rather than relying solely on test coverage
    // (task-2544 convention, memory id 0773d3a8; mirrors
    // `BucklingOptions.n_modes > 0`).
    constraint n_modes > 0
    // `tol` is the eigensolver convergence tolerance ‚Äî must be strictly
    // positive for the residual test to terminate. Zero or negative would
    // silently exhaust `max_iters` on every solve. Mirrors
    // `BucklingOptions.tol > 0`.
    constraint tol > 0
    // A non-positive `max_iters` would let the solver exit before doing any
    // work ‚Äî same degenerate failure mode as `BucklingOptions.max_iters <= 0`.
    // Same task-2544 rationale as above.
    constraint max_iters > 0
    // NOTE ‚Äî explicitly NOT constrained:
    //   sigma               : Real                  ‚Äî spectral-shift origin;
    //                          any real is physically valid (negative shifts
    //                          target the negative side of the spectrum).
    //                          `sigma >= 0` would wrongly forbid that, so the
    //                          contract stays open (mirrors
    //                          BucklingOptions.sigma).
    //   reference_direction : Vector3<Dimensionless> ‚Äî the `norm() > 0`
    //                          invariant is a method-call on Vector3, NOT a
    //                          scalar predicate, so it is NOT expressible in
    //                          Reify's `constraint` grammar. Deferred to the
    //                          runtime trampoline (future task Œ∂) per plan
    //                          design-decision-4, mirroring the
    //                          `BucklingOptions.mode` allowlist-deferral
    //                          precedent (solver_buckling.ri:97-107).
    //   damping             : DampingDescriptor     ‚Äî trait-typed; not
    //                          scalar-predicable.
    //   boundary_conditions : List<Support>         ‚Äî collection of trait
    //                          objects; not scalar-predicable.
}

// ‚îÄ‚îÄ ForcingFunction (marker trait) ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ

// `ForcingFunction` is the marker trait for the four transient-forcing
// primitives declared below (PRD ¬ß5.1 / task Œ∑):
//
//   - `StepForce`     ‚Äî unit-step force application at a given location
//   - `ImpulseForce`  ‚Äî Dirac-delta impulse (instantaneous momentum transfer)
//   - `HarmonicForce` ‚Äî sinusoidal harmonic force F(t) = A¬∑sin(œât + œÜ)
//   - `SampledForce`  ‚Äî non-uniform-sample table (Duhamel/Newmark-Œ≤ fallback)
//
// Kept empty by design (no required members): each conformer carries its own
// per-strategy fields; the trait exists only to give the `sources` param on
// `ForcingTimeHistory` a single nominal type-tag, so that
// `sources : List<ForcingFunction>` resolves to
// `Type::List(Box::new(Type::TraitObject("ForcingFunction")))` at compile
// time and the eval-time dispatch matches via the SIR-Œ± nominal type-tag.
//
// Same marker-trait pattern as `trait DampingDescriptor { }` (line 82) and
// `trait Support { }` (fea_types.ri).
//
// PRD reference: docs/prds/v0_3/modal-analysis.md ¬ß5.1.
trait ForcingFunction { }

// ‚îÄ‚îÄ StepForce ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ

// `StepForce` applies a unit-step forcing function at a given location on the
// part (PRD ¬ß5.1). The force is zero before `start_time` and constant at
// `magnitude` (in the `direction`) from `start_time` onward.
//
// Param semantics (PRD ¬ß5.1):
//   at         ‚Äî the location on the part where the force is applied.
//                FIXME(location-id-type, #4577): encoded as `String` PLACEHOLDER for
//                the future `LocationId` topology-selector type (not yet landed
//                in Reify v0.3). Consistent with `FixedSupport.target : String`
//                (fea_multi_case.ri:309) and `ModalResult.part : String`
//                (modal_analysis.ri:241) using `String` as a selector/name
//                placeholder. Consumer tasks Œ∏/Œπ read `.magnitude` and
//                `.direction`, not `.at` directly, so this placeholder is
//                non-blocking.
//   direction  ‚Äî unit excitation vector (no dimension ‚Äî a unit vector is
//                genuinely dimensionless). Encoded as
//                `Vector3<Dimensionless>` per the
//                `ModalOptions.reference_direction : Vector3<Dimensionless>`
//                precedent (modal_analysis.ri:358). The `direction.norm() > 0`
//                invariant is NOT expressible in Reify's constraint grammar
//                (method-call on Vector3, not a scalar predicate; same limit
//                as `reference_direction.norm() > 0` deferred in
//                modal_analysis.ri:382-389).
//   magnitude  ‚Äî positive scalar force size. By convention, `direction`
//                carries the sign (via the unit vector) and `magnitude`
//                carries the positive size. The `constraint magnitude > 0N`
//                lands in the next impl step (step-6).
//   start_time ‚Äî the time at which the step force switches on. Any real time
//                is valid; negative values support pre-loaded-history
//                simulations where the force has been applied before t=0.
//
// Refines `ForcingFunction` so that `sources : List<ForcingFunction>` on
// `ForcingTimeHistory` resolves correctly via the SIR-Œ± nominal type-tag.
//
// PRD reference: docs/prds/v0_3/modal-analysis.md ¬ß5.1.
structure def StepForce : ForcingFunction {
    param at : String
    param direction : Vector3<Dimensionless>
    param magnitude : Force
    param start_time : Time

    // By convention, `direction : Vector3<Dimensionless>` is the unit vector
    // that carries the sign of the force; `magnitude : Force` carries the
    // positive scalar size. A negative magnitude is meaningless when direction
    // is the sign-carrying unit vector. Declaring the lower bound at the
    // structure-def level makes the contract explicit in production code
    // rather than relying solely on test coverage (task-2544 convention,
    // mirroring `ModalOptions.n_modes > 0` at modal_analysis.ri:365 and
    // `PiecewisePolynomialProfile.waypoints.count > 0` at trajectory.ri:230).
    // Dimensioned literal `0N` (= 0 newtons in SI) is required to keep
    // eval_cmp dim-equality matching at runtime; a bare `0` would yield
    // `Indeterminate` per task #3115 esc-3115-112 (structural_physical.ri:67-68).
    constraint magnitude > 0N

    // NOTE ‚Äî explicitly NOT constrained:
    //   at         : String ‚Äî no scalar invariant expressible on a String
    //                         placeholder (LocationId not yet landed)
    //   direction  : Vector3<Dimensionless> ‚Äî `direction.norm() > 0` is a
    //                method-call on Vector3, not a scalar predicate; NOT
    //                expressible in Reify's constraint grammar (same limit as
    //                `reference_direction.norm() > 0` deferred in
    //                modal_analysis.ri:382-389).
    //   start_time : Time ‚Äî any real time is valid; negative values support
    //                pre-loaded-history simulations where the force has been
    //                applied before t=0.
}

// ‚îÄ‚îÄ ImpulseForce ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ

// `ImpulseForce` applies a Dirac-delta impulse at a given location on the
// part (PRD ¬ß5.1). Physically, an impulse is an instantaneous transfer of
// momentum: F(t) = impulse ¬∑ Œ¥(t ‚àí time), where Œ¥ is the Dirac delta.
//
// Param semantics (PRD ¬ß5.1):
//   at       ‚Äî the location on the part. FIXME(location-id-type, #4577): `String`
//              PLACEHOLDER for the future `LocationId` type (same convention
//              as `StepForce.at` above).
//   direction ‚Äî unit excitation vector. `Vector3<Dimensionless>` per the
//              `ModalOptions.reference_direction` precedent. The `direction`
//              unit-vector carries the sign; `impulse` carries the positive
//              scalar magnitude.
//   impulse  ‚Äî the positive scalar impulse (momentum transfer). Typed as
//              `Impulse` = N¬∑s = momentum = kg¬∑m¬∑s‚Åª¬π, registered in
//              NAMED_DIMENSIONS (crates/reify-core/src/dimension.rs, task 4548).
//              The `direction` unit-vector carries the sign; `impulse` carries
//              the positive scalar magnitude.
//   time     ‚Äî the time of the delta-function impulse application. Any real
//              time is valid; negative values support pre-loaded-history
//              simulations.
//
// PRD reference: docs/prds/v0_3/modal-analysis.md ¬ß5.1.
structure def ImpulseForce : ForcingFunction {
    param at : String
    param direction : Vector3<Dimensionless>
    param impulse : Impulse
    param time : Time

    // `impulse : Impulse` uses the dimensioned-zero form `0 * 1N * 1s`
    // (N¬∑s = kg¬∑m¬∑s‚Åª¬π = Impulse) because polymorphic-zero has not landed ‚Äî
    // same convention as `frequency > 0Hz` on the Frequency-typed
    // HarmonicForce.frequency and `StepForce.magnitude > 0N` above. By
    // convention, `direction` carries the sign (unit vector); `impulse` carries
    // the positive scalar magnitude. Declaring the lower bound at the
    // structure-def level follows the task-2544 explicit-contract convention.
    constraint impulse > 0 * 1N * 1s

    // NOTE ‚Äî explicitly NOT constrained:
    //   at        : String ‚Äî no scalar invariant expressible on a String placeholder
    //   direction : Vector3<Dimensionless> ‚Äî norm() is not scalar-predicable
    //   time      : Time ‚Äî any real time is valid; negative values support
    //                pre-loaded-history simulations (force applied before t=0)
}

// ‚îÄ‚îÄ HarmonicForce ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ

// `HarmonicForce` applies a sinusoidal forcing function at a given location
// on the part (PRD ¬ß5.1):
//
//     F(t) = amplitude ¬∑ sin(2œÄ ¬∑ frequency ¬∑ t + phase)
//
// Param semantics (PRD ¬ß5.1):
//   at        ‚Äî the application location. FIXME(location-id-type, #4577): `String`
//               PLACEHOLDER per the StepForce/ImpulseForce precedent.
//   direction ‚Äî unit excitation vector. `Vector3<Dimensionless>` per the
//               `ModalOptions.reference_direction` precedent. Direction carries
//               the sign; amplitude carries the positive peak size.
//   amplitude ‚Äî peak force magnitude (must be strictly positive). Encoded as
//               `Force` (bare dimension name per `io.ri:77` precedent). The
//               PRD ¬ß5.1 user-observable signal example explicitly states
//               `HarmonicForce(amplitude: -1N, ...)` should produce a
//               constraint-violation diagnostic ‚Äî the `constraint amplitude > 0N`
//               is the production-code manifestation of that signal.
//   frequency ‚Äî cycles per second (must be strictly positive). A zero-frequency
//               "harmonic" is a DC offset (physically degenerate as a sinusoid);
//               negative frequency is degenerate (symmetric to positive under the
//               sine function). Encoded as `Frequency` (bare dimension name).
//   phase     ‚Äî initial phase offset in angle units. Default `0deg` (zero Angle
//               literal) per PRD ¬ß5.1 "default: 0". The canonical zero-Angle
//               default `= 0deg` (not bare `= 0`) is required because a bare `0`
//               yields `Type::Real` which is dim-incompatible with `Type::Scalar
//               { ANGLE }` per task #3115 esc-3115-112 (structural_physical.ri:
//               67-68 documents the same reasoning). Choice of `deg` over `rad`
//               follows `tolerancing.ri:113` precedent and is more user-intuitive
//               for the typical 0/90/180 phase-offset workflow. Any real phase
//               value is physically valid (phase is modular 2œÄ), so phase is NOT
//               constrained.
//
// PRD reference: docs/prds/v0_3/modal-analysis.md ¬ß5.1.
structure def HarmonicForce : ForcingFunction {
    param at : String
    param direction : Vector3<Dimensionless>
    param amplitude : Force
    param frequency : Frequency
    param phase : Angle = 0deg

    // PRD ¬ß5.1 user-observable signal: `HarmonicForce(amplitude: -1N, ...)`
    // must produce a constraint-violation diagnostic. Direction carries the
    // sign (unit vector); amplitude carries the positive peak size. Declaring
    // the lower bound at the structure-def level follows the task-2544
    // explicit-contract convention (same rationale as `StepForce.magnitude
    // > 0N` and `ModalOptions.n_modes > 0`). Dimensioned literal `0N`
    // required per structural_physical.ri:67-68.
    constraint amplitude > 0N

    // A zero-frequency "harmonic" is a DC offset (degenerate as a sinusoid);
    // negative frequency is symmetric to positive under sin() and physically
    // degenerate for a "harmonic" excitation. Dimensioned literal `0Hz`
    // required per the same dim-equality rationale as `amplitude > 0N`.
    constraint frequency > 0Hz

    // NOTE ‚Äî explicitly NOT constrained:
    //   at        : String ‚Äî no scalar invariant expressible on a String placeholder
    //   direction : Vector3<Dimensionless> ‚Äî norm() not scalar-predicable
    //   phase     : Angle  ‚Äî physically modular 2œÄ; any real value is valid
    //                (a negative phase offset is meaningful in the context of
    //                two overlapping HarmonicForce sources)
}

// ‚îÄ‚îÄ SampledForce ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ

// `SampledForce` applies a time-varying force described by non-uniform sample
// tables (PRD ¬ß5.1 / ¬ß5.3). The Duhamel-integral / Newmark-Œ≤ transient
// trampoline (task Œ∏) interpolates linearly between samples at each solver
// timestep.
//
// Param semantics (PRD ¬ß5.1 / ¬ß5.3):
//   at           ‚Äî application location. FIXME(location-id-type, #4577): `String`
//                  PLACEHOLDER per the StepForce precedent.
//   direction    ‚Äî unit excitation vector. `Vector3<Dimensionless>` per the
//                  `ModalOptions.reference_direction` precedent. Direction
//                  carries the sign; force_samples carry the positive scalar
//                  magnitudes.
//   time_samples ‚Äî non-uniform time stamps at which force is specified.
//                  `List<Time>` (bare dimension name `Time` per `io.ri:77`
//                  precedent). Must be non-empty (empty ‚â° degenerate, no force
//                  data); the constraint `time_samples.count > 0` lands in
//                  step-18. The `count` method on `List` is recognised in
//                  constraint position per `reify-expr/src/lib.rs:1349`
//                  evaluator arm; precedent:
//                  `PiecewisePolynomialProfile.constraint waypoints.count > 0`
//                  (trajectory.ri:230).
//   force_samples ‚Äî force magnitudes at the corresponding time stamps.
//                  `List<Force>`. Must be non-empty (same rationale).
//
// Cross-list invariant NOTE: `time_samples.count == force_samples.count` is NOT
// expressible in Reify's constraint grammar ‚Äî the `constraint` clause admits
// only scalar predicates over single cells in the same scope, and "two same-
// structure cells equal" requires the eval-time machinery of the transient_
// response trampoline (future task Œ∏). Deferred there intentionally.
//
// PRD reference: docs/prds/v0_3/modal-analysis.md ¬ß5.1, ¬ß5.3.
structure def SampledForce : ForcingFunction {
    param at : String
    param direction : Vector3<Dimensionless>
    param time_samples : List<Time>
    param force_samples : List<Force>

    // Empty `time_samples` is degenerate: no force data can be reconstructed
    // from zero samples. Declared at structure-def level to catch the failure
    // at construction rather than waiting for the transient_response trampoline
    // (task Œ∏). Mirrors `PiecewisePolynomialProfile.constraint waypoints.count
    // > 0` (trajectory.ri:230). The `.count` method on `List` is recognised in
    // constraint position per `reify-expr/src/lib.rs:1349` evaluator arm.
    constraint time_samples.count > 0

    // Same rationale as time_samples.count > 0 above. An empty force_samples
    // list with a non-empty time_samples list would also be degenerate.
    constraint force_samples.count > 0

    // NOTE ‚Äî explicitly NOT constrained:
    //   at          : String ‚Äî no scalar invariant expressible on a String placeholder
    //   direction   : Vector3<Dimensionless> ‚Äî norm() not scalar-predicable
    //   Cross-list invariant time_samples.count == force_samples.count ‚Äî NOT
    //   expressible in Reify constraint grammar (single-cell scalar predicates
    //   only; "two same-structure cells equal" requires eval-time machinery).
    //   Deferred to the transient_response trampoline (task Œ∏).
}

// ‚îÄ‚îÄ ForcingTimeHistory ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ

// `ForcingTimeHistory` is the additive aggregate container for all forcing
// sources acting on a single Part during a transient simulation (PRD ¬ß5.1).
// It bundles N `ForcingFunction`-conforming sources (StepForce, ImpulseForce,
// HarmonicForce, SampledForce, or any future conformer) at the per-Part layer.
//
// Param semantics (PRD ¬ß5.1):
//   part    ‚Äî the Part on which the forcing history acts.
//             FIXME(part-structdef, #4578): encoded as `String` PLACEHOLDER for the
//             future `Part` topology type (not yet landed in Reify v0.3).
//             Consistent with `ModalResult.part : String` (modal_analysis.ri:
//             241) and `ModalOptions.part : String` using `String` as a
//             selector/name placeholder. Consumer tasks Œ∏/Œπ locate the DOF
//             assembly via this string at runtime.
//   sources ‚Äî list of forcing sources that sum linearly at each (t, location)
//             pair per PRD ¬ß12.5 resolved-question ("sources sum linearly; no
//             cross-source coupling in modal superposition"). Encoded as
//             `List<ForcingFunction>` which resolves at compile time to
//             `Type::List(Box::new(Type::TraitObject("ForcingFunction")))` ‚Äî
//             same shape as `ModalResult.boundary_conditions : List<Support>`
//             (modal_analysis.ri:243) which resolves to
//             `Type::List(Box::new(Type::TraitObject("Support")))`. The
//             `constraint sources.count > 0` lands in step-22; an empty
//             sources list corresponds to the PRD ¬ß1 `E_TransientForcingMissing`
//             diagnostic.
//
// Design note: `ForcingTimeHistory` does NOT refine `ForcingFunction`. It is
// the AGGREGATE container, not a forcing primitive. Only the four conformers
// (StepForce, ImpulseForce, HarmonicForce, SampledForce) carry `: ForcingFunction`.
// Keeping the two layers separate allows `sources : List<ForcingFunction>` to
// remain a homogeneous trait-object list, and prevents accidental recursive
// nesting (a ForcingTimeHistory is NOT itself a source within another history).
//
// PRD reference: docs/prds/v0_3/modal-analysis.md ¬ß5.1.
structure def ForcingTimeHistory {
    param part : String
    param sources : List<ForcingFunction>

    // An empty `sources` list corresponds exactly to the PRD ¬ß1
    // `E_TransientForcingMissing` diagnostic: there is nothing to simulate.
    // Declaring the lower bound at the structure-def level catches the failure
    // at construction (via SIR-Œ±'s `check_constraints_against_templates`,
    // task 3540, already landed) rather than waiting for the transient_response
    // trampoline (task Œ∏) to flag it. Follows the task-2544 explicit-contract
    // convention, mirroring `PiecewisePolynomialProfile.constraint
    // waypoints.count > 0` (trajectory.ri:230) and
    // `SampledForce.constraint time_samples.count > 0` above.
    constraint sources.count > 0

    // NOTE ‚Äî explicitly NOT constrained:
    //   part : String ‚Äî no scalar invariant expressible on a String placeholder;
    //                   the future `Part` tighten target does not change this.
    //   Cross-source temporal-overlap semantics (sources summing linearly at
    //   each (t, location) per PRD ¬ß12.5 resolved-question) are runtime
    //   semantics, not a structure-def scalar predicate; deferred to the
    //   transient_response trampoline (task Œ∏).
}

// ‚îÄ‚îÄ DisplacementTimeHistory ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ

// `DisplacementTimeHistory` is the transient-response solver-output container
// (PRD ¬ß5.2 / ¬ß10 task Œπ) ‚Äî the modal-superposition twin of `ModalResult`. It
// bundles the per-mode modal-coordinate time histories Œæ_i(t_j) produced by the
// `transient_response` trampoline together with the modal basis they were
// integrated against, so a downstream `displacement_at(history, location,
// direction)` query can lazily reconstruct the physical displacement
// u(t_j) = Œ£_i (Œ¶_i[node]¬∑direction)¬∑Œæ_i(t_j) at a SINGLE location without ever
// materializing the full n_nodes √ó n_times displacement matrix.
//
// Declared after `ModalResult` (above) so the `modal_result : ModalResult` field
// resolves in-file. Solver-populated only: every field is determined by the
// transient solve, so no caller-supplied defaults are meaningful and no scalar
// constraints are declared at the structure-def level (mirrors `ModalResult`).
// The meaningful invariants are COLLECTION invariants (`mode_coords` outer length
// == `modal_result.modes` count, every inner length == `t_samples` count) which
// Reify's `constraint` grammar cannot express (scalar predicates over same-scope
// cells only); they are producer-enforced by the `transient_response` trampoline
// (task Œπ), mirroring the `ModalResult.modes` discipline.
//
// Field semantics (PRD ¬ß5.2):
//   part         ‚Äî the analysed part. FIXME(part-structdef, #4578): encoded as `String`
//                  PLACEHOLDER for the future `Part` type, identical to
//                  `ModalResult.part` (modal_analysis.ri:241) and
//                  `ForcingTimeHistory.part`. The trampoline echoes it from the
//                  modal result (currently the `""` placeholder).
//   modal_result ‚Äî the `ModalResult` the response was integrated against, echoed
//                  verbatim so `displacement_at` can read each mode's `shape`
//                  (Œ¶_i) for the projection coefficient Œ¶_i[node]¬∑direction
//                  without re-running the eigensolve. Resolves to
//                  `StructureRef("ModalResult")` (declared above).
//   t_samples    ‚Äî the uniform time grid the response was sampled on, one entry
//                  per timestep. `List<Time>` (bare dimension name `Time` per the
//                  `SampledForce.time_samples : List<Time>` precedent above). The
//                  grid is produced by the trampoline from (t_start, t_end, dt).
//   mode_coords  ‚Äî the per-mode modal-coordinate time histories: `mode_coords[i]`
//                  is the scalar Œæ_i(t_j) series for mode `i` (outer index = mode,
//                  inner index = timestep), so the outer length equals the modal
//                  count and each inner length equals `t_samples.count`. Encoded
//                  as `List<List<Real>>` ‚Äî a nested-generic list, valid per the
//                  `Tensegrity.struts : List<List<Int>>` (tensegrity.ri:76) and
//                  `MotionEnvelope.nominal_pose : List<List<Pose3>>`
//                  (trajectory.ri:322) precedents. `Real` (not a dimensioned
//                  scalar) because a mass-normalized modal coordinate Œæ_i carries
//                  units of ‚àömass¬∑length (the dual of `Mode.shape`'s 1/‚àömass
//                  components), not expressible in Reify's dimension grammar ‚Äî
//                  the same unrepresentable-SI-root limitation `Mode.shape`
//                  documents (modal_analysis.ri:155-165).
//
// PRD reference: docs/prds/v0_3/modal-analysis.md ¬ß5.2.
structure def DisplacementTimeHistory {
    param part : String
    param modal_result : ModalResult
    param t_samples : List<Time>
    param mode_coords : List<List<Real>>
    // NOTE ‚Äî explicitly NOT constrained:
    //   part         : String      ‚Äî no scalar invariant expressible on a String
    //                                 placeholder; the future `Part` tighten
    //                                 target does not change this.
    //   modal_result : ModalResult ‚Äî struct-typed; not scalar-predicable.
    //   t_samples / mode_coords    ‚Äî collection invariants (`mode_coords` outer
    //                                 length == modes count, each inner length ==
    //                                 `t_samples` count) are NOT expressible in
    //                                 Reify's constraint grammar (single-cell
    //                                 scalar predicates only); producer-enforced
    //                                 by the transient_response trampoline
    //                                 (task Œπ), mirroring the ModalResult.modes
    //                                 discipline (modal_analysis.ri:248-258).
}
